    <div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='5311#1217518528'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2008-07-31T15:35:28+00:00">Jul 31, 2008 03:35 PM UTC</time> by <b>Tim Silvers</b><a class="anchor" name="1217518528">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>This was resolved at 10&#58;27AM (14&#58;27 UTC). I had noticed around 10AM that the BDII data on Bundy
was over eight hours old, putting the time of the failure at roughly 1&#58;44AM EDT (05&#58;44 UTC). The
server had gone into a read-only state, which is the same issue we had when the production
instance of this service was on Dahmer.

We moved production to Bundy a few weeks ago hoping that it would stabilize the service since we
had not yet experienced the problem in the ITB environment hosted on Bundy. However, the
problem has followed us to Bundy.

While the cause remains a mystery, Tom is investigating some potential causes. Both kernels on
these Gentoo machines are different, and they&#39;re several versions old. Currently 2.1.x versions
(2.1.6 and 2.1.7 if I recall) and the newest is 2.6.x. Also, there are some firmware updates that we
might need to apply.

It&#39;s rather obvious that we need to stabilize this service. Efforts are being made to do so, but more
occurrences could happen before such time. We have several monitors in place, but none catch the
read-only error. Munin may be able to help us by sending email if the load average drops below .6;
the average load is typically around 1.0 but does drop to around a .8 under normal operations. This
outage was first noticed by me when I went to the server to get data in the process of testing the
newer test instance of the BDII I&#39;ve setup on Riley at IUPUI. Then the NOC picked up on it with the
Nagios alert during the reboot, which we should have alerted them was going to happen.

I am closing this ticket at this time.

Tim</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='5311#1217515935'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2008-07-31T14:52:15+00:00">Jul 31, 2008 02:52 PM UTC</time> by <b>Joseph Brown</b><a class="anchor" name="1217515935">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Service Ok[07-31-2008 14&#58;43&#58;21] SERVICE ALERT&#58; bundy.uits.indiana.edu;TCP PORT
